Package: scimesh
Type: Package
Title: Headless 3D Mesh Rendering Engine
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Tim", "Schaefer", email = "ts@example.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Author: Tim Schaefer
Maintainer: Tim Schaefer <ts@example.com>
Description: A minimal, fast, headless 3D software renderer written in modern
    C++ with native R bindings. Serves as a zero-dependency, fallback rendering
    engine for 3D meshes when traditional GPU-backed frameworks are unavailable.
    Produces in-memory RGBA images suitable for scientific visualization.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 1.0.0)
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    png
SystemRequirements: C++17
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Encoding: UTF-8
NeedsCompilation: yes
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
